2. DATA — PROPRIETARY THIRD-PARTY SOURCES (NOT COVERED BY THIS LICENSE)
================================================================================

This research relies on commercial datasets that are the property of their
respective providers and are licensed for academic use through Wharton Research
Data Services (WRDS). These datasets are NOT owned by the author, are NOT
licensed to third parties under this file, and are NOT redistributed in this
repository. No raw vendor data is included here; only derived, aggregated
research outputs sufficient to document the analysis are retained.

The data providers and their materials include:

  - LSEG (London Stock Exchange Group) — earnings call transcripts.
    © LSEG. All rights reserved.

  - I/B/E/S (Institutional Brokers' Estimate System), provided via LSEG —
    analyst estimates and standardized unexpected earnings (SUE).
    © LSEG / I/B/E/S. All rights reserved.

  - CRSP (Center for Research in Security Prices, LLC) — daily stock returns
    and security identifiers.
    © CRSP, an affiliate of the University of Chicago Booth School of Business.
    All rights reserved.

  - Compustat, provided via S&P Global Market Intelligence — quarterly
    fundamentals.
    © S&P Global Market Intelligence. All rights reserved.

Use of each dataset is governed by the terms of the applicable WRDS
subscription and the data provider's own license agreement. Any person wishing
to reproduce this research must obtain independent, valid licenses to these
datasets directly from the providers or through WRDS. Nothing in this
repository grants, transfers, or implies any right to use the underlying
proprietary data.

The Loughran-McDonald Master Dictionary is used under the terms made available
by its authors (Loughran & McDonald, 2011) and remains the property of its
authors.

